column5: It was the Central Canada Outdoors Show up here today, made it by for the first time in the 5 yrs it has been happening. Picked this up, and a couple packages of imitation baits, now I gotta figure out how the damn contraption works.
nice unit! u wont be disappointed with it!! enjoy!
Heh, Heh, maybe I should have bought it Friday night, the opening of the show, it might have secured me a trout for my team, no guarantees on that though,  lol
you'll love it!   i dont know how ive fished so long wihtout mine!

Congrats Tom. There's no bad units out there these days only verying degrees of good, better and best.  But everyone of them is better than going blind. I'm sure you'll have it figured out in no time.

Watch out with the 2 cables going to the transducer..... sometimes the wrong one takes the weight of the 'ducer and causes it to sit unlevel (and you won't mark properly).  I ended up removing the support cable altogether.
yeah ...listen to Ben it really does make a difference ... i have the ice 45 and its great
it was a good choice to not get the 35.  enjoy! sometimes it helps and other days it just frustrates, but it's always fun.
Nice Machine. I'm sure it will do you well on the ice for the coming years!
